    "### What is Iterative Imputation?\n",
    "\n",
    "Iterative imputation is a technique where missing values are filled in by modeling each feature with missing values as a function of the other features in the dataset. Instead of filling missing values with simple statistics (like mean or median), iterative imputation works by leveraging the information in other variables to predict the missing values, and then iterates to refine these predictions.\n",
    "\n",
    "It’s a model-based approach that can be more accurate, especially when there are complex relationships among features. The goal of iterative imputation is to create realistic estimates for missing values, helping you build a more reliable dataset for analysis or machine learning tasks."
   ]
  },
